Subject: Derived Integration Disposition Worker Latch Source

Description: Preserved derived source for the integration_disposition_015 worker latch observed during LM Studio corpus benchmarking.

& [DerivedIntegrationDispositionWorkerLatchSource] is preserved derived source
  + [source_type] is derived_from_benchmark_observation
  + [observed_subject] is corpus_integration_disposition_015
  + [initial_failure] is worker produced all requested fields but called validation pass despite a missing required literal term and left outside empty
  + [retry_001_failure] is worker repaired the disposition meaning but removed the two-space property-line prefix and failed raw SOP format
  + [accepted_retry] is retry 002 passed after the prompt emphasized failed validation, retry disposition, populated outside, forbidden phrase avoidance, and exact two-space property-line prefixes
  + [derived_latches] is validation_status_truth_latch, outside_content_latch, forbidden_phrase_avoidance_latch, property_line_prefix_latch, and ASCII stability check
  + [reason_for_change] is integration disposition tasks need strict separation of validation status, integration disposition, evidence, outside, and authority before worker output can become readiness evidence
  + [outside] is hidden model state, broad LM Studio competence, project-root authority, worker mutation authority, credentials, destructive action, self-integration, direct trust, and broad readiness synthesis

  = must: preserve failed attempts as benchmark data
  = must: treat retry success as one family signal only
  = must: keep Codex as validator and integration authority
  - never: let a worker integrate its own output or claim repository authority
